# UI Workflow — always read

Before doing UI work in this worktree, follow **`docs/UI-WORKFLOW.md`** (the
canonical reference). Key non-negotiables, inline so they're never missed:

- **Worktree setup:** `cp ~/virtuna-v1.1/.env.local .` + link/install
  `node_modules` (`ln -s ~/virtuna-v1.1/node_modules ./node_modules` or
  `pnpm install`). Skip this and `tsc`/`vitest` run as stubs → **false green.**
- **Lanes (don't cross):** `lane/polish`=tokens + `globals.css` + `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` ·
  `lane/frame`=landing/auth/settings/billing · `lane/shell`=nav/chrome/error/skeletons/motion ·
  `lane/cursor-ui`=small refinement. The **GSI milestone** (`milestone/numen-gsi`) owns the core
  verb surfaces + `src/lib/**` + `src/app/api/**` + `supabase/**` — see the HOLD list in
  `ui-design.mdc` §3a; polish those via the token seam only, never fork-edit.
- **Auto-wip daemon: never inside a lane worktree** — it co-opts the live branch (the PR #60 lesson).
- **Design system locked:** flat-warm charcoal, accent terracotta `#d97757` at
  near-zero dosage. Source of truth = `globals.css` + `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`.
  Keep `reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` green.
- **Verify visually**, never "should work." Rebase on `main` often (GSI merges `main` at each phase
  boundary); keep PRs small and per-surface; merge promptly.

## To turn this off

